The global E-Scooter, Moped, and E-Motorcycle market are witnessing significant growth, driven by increasing urbanization, rising environmental concerns, and the need for energy-efficient modes of transportation. The market is segmented into E-Scooters and E-Motorcycles, each with its subcategories based on type, battery type, voltage, and technology.

E-Scooters are further classified into retro, standing/self-balancing, and folding types, with battery options including sealed lead-acid and Li-Ion, and voltage variations of 36V, 48V, 60V, and 72V. On the other hand, E-Motorcycles are categorized by battery type (sealed lead-acid, Li-Ion), voltage (36V, 48V, 60V, 72V), and technology (battery, plug-in).

