In the E-Scooter segment, we observe a further breakdown based on type, battery type, and voltage. The types of E-Scooters include retro models, standing/self-balancing designs, and folding variants, catering to different consumer preferences and usage scenarios. Additionally, the choice of battery type is crucial in determining the performance and range of E-Scooters, with options ranging from sealed lead-acid batteries to the more advanced Li-Ion batteries. The voltage specifications further differentiate E-Scooters, with variants available at 36V, 48V, 60V, and 72V, offering varying levels of power output and efficiency.

Moving on to the E-Motorcycle market, the segmentation is based on battery type, voltage, and technology. These electric motorcycles are equipped with either sealed lead-acid batteries or Li-Ion batteries, with the latter being more favored for their superior performance and energy density. Voltage specifications play a crucial role in determining the speed and power capabilities of E-Motorcycles, with options including 36V, 48V, 60V, and 72V models. Furthermore, the technology aspect distinguishes E-Motorcycles based on battery-driven systems or plug-in variants, offering consumers flexibility in charging and usage.

